article.description: Yoeli Childs scored 19 points and grabbed a dozen rebounds as BYU opened West Coast Conference play by walloping Loyola Marymount, 63-38 on Saturday night.
article.headline: BYU opens WCC play by walloping Loyola Marymount, 63-38
article.linkText: BYU opens WCC play by walloping Loyola Marymount, 63-38
article.story: PROVO, Utah -- Yoeli Childs scored 19 points and grabbed a dozen rebounds as BYU opened West Coast Conference play by walloping Loyola Marymount, 63-38 on Saturday night. The Cougars recorded their sixth straight win by limiting the Lions to just 19 points in each half. Loyola Marymount shot just 34% from the field, hitting 16 of 47, including just 2 of 15 from long range. Jake Toolson scored 13 points and collected five steals for BYU (12-4), which shot 23 of 54 from the field (42.6%) and hit 8 of 24 from behind the arc. Eli Scott had 15 points for the Lions (7-9, 1-1).
